# Split ownership for anti-PR-escalation (see .data/specs/roles-and-capabilities.md).
# Replace the placeholder handles with real GitHub usernames or teams at M0.
#
# Superadmin-owned (admins cannot self-promote): roles, CODEOWNERS, CI, and root config.
/CODEOWNERS              @atwellpub @gbtilabs
/.github/                @atwellpub @gbtilabs
/house/roles.yml         @atwellpub @gbtilabs
/astro.config.mjs        @atwellpub @gbtilabs
/package.json            @atwellpub @gbtilabs
/src/                    @atwellpub @gbtilabs
/scripts/                @atwellpub @gbtilabs

# Admin-owned: bans, grandfather, and the rest of house/. The two superadmins own both tiers
# until a separate admin team exists (swap an @org/admins team in here later without touching
# the superadmin-owned paths above).
/house/                  @atwellpub @gbtilabs

# SOW-087: brand-reach controls (the category -> Discord-channel map + the moderation word lists) are
# superadmin-tier by intent; the two superadmins own them explicitly even if /house/ is later delegated.
/house/content-channels.yml  @atwellpub @gbtilabs
/house/moderation-flags.yml  @atwellpub @gbtilabs
# SOW-022: applets are a SUPERADMIN-only content type (GBTI does not host member code). Explicit so the rule
# holds even if /house/ is later delegated to an admin team. The collection glob also excludes member folders,
# and validate-content rejects any members/*/applets/.
/house/applets/          @atwellpub @gbtilabs

# members/<username>/ is author-scoped by the gate + scripts/validate-content.mjs, not by CODEOWNERS.
